4 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana hereby amends
5 LAC 55:I.207 to read as follows:
6 A. A request for the bureau to conduct a criminal history check authorized by R.S.
7 40:1203.2 shall be made on a form provided by the bureau and submitted to it by an
8 employer or authorized agency.
9 B. Each request for a criminal history check authorized by R.S. 40:1203.2 submitted
10 to the bureau shall be accompanied by the fee of twenty-six dollars as established by R.S.
11 40:1203.2(B)(2) and LAC 55:I.101.A and a five dollar technology fee as established by R.S.
12 15:587(D).
13 C. Each request for a criminal history check submitted to the bureau by an authorized
14 agency shall be accompanied by a letter of engagement or contract with the employer as
15 proof that the authorized agency may request and receive criminal history information on
16 behalf of the employer. The results of each criminal history check submitted by an
17 authorized agency on behalf of an employer will be reported to the authorized agency.
18 D. Any Effective beginning October 1, 2026, any criminal history check that
19 contains possible arrest information, shall be resubmitted to the bureau for a fingerprint
20 based background check for positive verification.
21 E. Effective until October 1, 2026, the bureau shall allow parish and local law
22 enforcement agencies to perform criminal history checks and return the applicable
23 criminal history information to an authorized agency.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
25 office of state register.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Louisiana Register is hereby directed to have
27 the amendments to LAC 55:I.207 printed and incorporated into the Louisiana Administrative
28 Code and to transmit a copy of the revised rules to the Department of Public Safety and
29 Corrections.
